# MCP Tools Reference for 1C Development

This file describes available MCP tools for 1C development. Reference this file instead of duplicating tool descriptions.

## Code & Documentation Search

| Tool | Alias | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-------|---------|-------------|
| **docsearch** | — | Search 1C platform documentation | Verify built-in function existence, check method signatures, find platform features |
| **search_code** | **codesearch** | Search existing configuration code (fulltext, semantic, hybrid) | Find patterns, check usages, verify implementations exist |
| **templatesearch** | — | Search code templates and examples | Find architectural patterns, get implementation examples before writing code |
| **ssl_search** | — | Search SSL (БСП) functions | Find standard library functions to reuse |
| **helpsearch** | — | Search help articles and user documentation | Find help topics, user-facing documentation |

> **Note**: Some tools have aliases. Use whichever name is available in your MCP server: `search_code` / `codesearch`, `search_metadata` / `metadatasearch`.

## Metadata Tools

| Tool | Alias | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-------|---------|-------------|
| **search_metadata** | **metadatasearch** | Search configuration metadata structure | Verify object existence, check attributes, find relationships |
| **get_metadata_prompt** | — | Get instructions for cypher query | When search_metadata unavailable |
| **execute_metadata_cypher** | — | Execute metadata cypher query | After get_metadata_prompt |
| **business_search** | — | Semantic search for metadata | Find objects by natural language description |
| **answer_metadata_question** | — | Get answers about metadata objects | Understand how metadata objects work |

## Code Quality Tools (SyntaxCheckServer)

| Tool | Alias | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-------|---------|-------------|
| **syntaxcheck** | — | Check BSL syntax and style via BSL Language Server | After writing code, verify no errors. **Limit: 3 times per cycle** |

## 1CCodeChecker Tools (1С:Напарник)

**11 tools** for code analysis, review, modification, and documentation access. These tools integrate with the 1С:Напарник service (code.1c.ai) and provide critical capabilities for high-quality 1C development.

### Code Analysis & Modification

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **check_1c_code** | Technical check: syntax, logic, performance | After writing code — find bugs and performance issues |
| **review_1c_code** | Code review: style, ITS standards, naming, structure | After writing code — ensure standards compliance |
| **rewrite_1c_code** | AI rewrites code with improvements (optional `goal`: `optimize`, `readability`, `error handling`) | When code needs significant improvement |
| **modify_1c_code** | Modify or generate code by explicit instruction | Apply targeted changes, fix specific bugs, add features |
| **ask_1c_ai** | Free-form question to 1С:Напарник (preserves dialog context) | Architecture questions, concept explanations, advice |

### Documentation & Knowledge Base

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **search_1c_documentation** | Search platform docs for specific version (e.g. `v8.3.25`) | Version-specific method signatures, platform features |
| **onec_help** | Search platform docs (latest version) | Quick lookup of platform features, methods, types |
| **its_help** | Search ITS knowledge base (standards, methodologies) | Find ITS standards, best practices. **Returns document IDs → use `fetch_its`** |
| **fetch_its** | Read full ITS document by ID | **Always use after `its_help`** to read found articles. Special IDs: `root`, `v8std` |
| **diff_1c_documentation_versions** | Compare docs between platform versions | Check changes between versions (e.g. `v8.3.25` → `v8.5.1`) |
| **config_help** | Search docs for specific configs (ERP, БП, ЗУП, УТ) | Config-specific business logic, object descriptions |

> **Key workflow**: `its_help` → get document IDs → `fetch_its` with each ID to read full content. Never ignore ITS article references.

## Tool Usage by Task

### Writing New Code
1. **templatesearch** — find similar implementations
2. **search_code** / **codesearch** — check existing patterns
3. **search_metadata** / **metadatasearch** — verify metadata structure
4. **docsearch** — verify built-in functions
5. **ssl_search** — find reusable SSL functions
6. **syntaxcheck** — verify syntax after writing
7. **check_1c_code** — find logic and performance issues
8. **review_1c_code** — verify style and standards compliance

### Code Review
1. **search_code** / **codesearch** — verify pattern compliance
2. **search_metadata** / **metadatasearch** — check correct metadata usage
3. **docsearch** — verify method/property existence
4. **review_1c_code** — check style and ITS standards compliance
5. **check_1c_code** — find bugs and performance issues
6. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — verify against ITS standards

### Architecture Design
1. **search_metadata** / **metadatasearch** — understand existing structure
2. **search_code** / **codesearch** — find existing patterns
3. **templatesearch** — find architectural templates
4. **ask_1c_ai** — get architectural advice from 1С:Напарник
5. **config_help** — understand how specific configurations implement patterns

### Documentation
1. **search_code** / **codesearch** — find code to document
2. **search_metadata** / **metadatasearch** — understand metadata structure
3. **docsearch** — reference platform documentation
4. **helpsearch** — find existing help articles
5. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — find and read ITS methodological articles
6. **search_1c_documentation** — find version-specific platform docs

### Error Fixing
1. **syntaxcheck** — identify syntax errors
2. **check_1c_code** — identify logic and performance problems
3. **docsearch** — verify correct function names
4. **search_metadata** / **metadatasearch** — verify metadata object names
5. **search_code** / **codesearch** — find correct usage patterns
6. **modify_1c_code** — apply targeted fixes via AI

### Performance Optimization
1. **search_code** / **codesearch** — find slow patterns
2. **search_metadata** / **metadatasearch** — check indexes
3. **check_1c_code** — analyze performance issues
4. **rewrite_1c_code** — get AI-optimized code (with `goal: optimize`)
5. **templatesearch** — find optimized patterns
6. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — find ITS performance standards

### Comparing Platform Versions
1. **diff_1c_documentation_versions** — see what changed between versions
2. **search_1c_documentation** — search docs for specific version

## Important Rules

1. **Always search before writing** — use templatesearch and search_code first
2. **Verify against documentation** — use docsearch for built-in functions
3. **Check metadata exists** — use search_metadata before using objects
4. **Limit syntaxcheck** — maximum 3 times per cycle, then move on
5. **Prefer search_metadata** — primary tool for metadata structure queries
6. **Don't use Grep** — when MCP tools are available for code search
7. **Always follow up `its_help` with `fetch_its`** — read full ITS article content by ID
8. **Use 1CCodeChecker tools actively** — `check_1c_code` and `review_1c_code` after every code change
